results.abstract: 5th yr in orbit marked, Jet Propulsion Lab; 1st US satellite, has outlasted all others, US or USSR; seen lasting 5 more yrs

headline.main: EXPLORER I ENDS 5TH YEAR IN ORBIT; Up Since '58, It Outlasts All U.S. and Soviet Satellites Orbit No. 24,090 The U.S.-Soviet Tally Three Successful Series Course Changed Little

results.snippet: PASADENA, Calif., Jan. 31 --The United States' first satellite, Explorer I, completed its fifth year in orbit today.

byline.original: By BILL BECKER Special to The New York Times

results.lead_paragraph: PASADENA, Calif., Jan. 31 --The United States' first satellite, Explorer I, completed its fifth year in orbit today.
